presentation_title: "The Vibe Coding Era: From Coder to Pilot"
target_audience: "Young Developers"
slides[15]:
- slide_number: 1
  heading: "The Provocation"
  points[3]:
    - "Why are you still hand-cranking code while the world is vibe coding?"
    - "The shift from 'writing lines' to 'steering intent'."
    - "The cost of staying 'manual' in an automated industry."
- slide_number: 2
  heading: "The Engine Analogy"
  points[4]:
    - "The Agent is the Car Engine: Raw power, speed, and torque."
    - "The Developer is the Driver: Steering, braking, and navigation."
    - "Logic is the chassis; without it, the engine (AI) will just twist the frame."
    - "A faster engine only makes a bad driver crash sooner."
- slide_number: 3
  heading: "The State of AI Adoption"
  points[3]:
    - "Visualizing the gap: AI Adopters vs. Traditional Coders."
    - "Industry stats on speed-to-market using coding agents."
    - "Why 'Agentic Workflows' are the 2026 standard."
- slide_number: 4
  heading: "Choosing Your Fuel (Model Tradeoffs)"
  points[3]:
    - "Cost vs. Quality: LLM comparison (o1/Pro vs. Flash/Haiku)."
    - "When to use High-Reasoning (Architecting) vs. High-Speed (Boilerplate)."
    - "Economic engineering: Don't burn a 'Pro' token on a 'Flash' task."
- slide_number: 5
  heading: "The Architecture of Intent (Markdowns)"
  points[4]:
    - "Agents: Defining the persona and expertise."
    - "Skills: Mapping what the agent can actually execute."
    - "Rules: The 'Hard Constraints' (Linting, Styles, Frameworks)."
    - "Markdown as the universal language for Agent instructions."
- slide_number: 6
  heading: "Context: Your Short-Term Memory"
  points[4]:
    - "Context is all that matters—preserve it like your own memory."
    - "Attach Files strategically: More context isn't always better context."
    - "Context Window Poisoning: How circular errors and logs kill AI logic."
    - "Integrity Checks: Validating what the AI 'remembers' before it acts."
- slide_number: 7
  heading: "Strategic Workflow: Act vs. Plan"
  points[3]:
    - "For complex tasks: Always demand a Markdown Plan first."
    - "The 'Human-in-the-Loop' (HITL) checkpoint: Verify the plan before execution."
    - "Avoiding the 'Refactoring Rampage': Never let an AI touch the whole project at once."
- slide_number: 8
  heading: "The Plumbing: MCPs vs. CLIs"
  points[4]:
    - "CLIs are the past; Model Context Protocol (MCP) is the future."
    - "Introduction to Context7: Up-to-date, version-specific documentation."
    - "The Challenge: Permissioning and state drift in agentic loops."
    - "Industry Trend: Moving toward the 'Model as the Environment'."
- slide_number: 9
  heading: "Full-Stack Vibe: Handling Multiple Stacks"
  points[3]:
    - "Single-Project Folders: Keeping Client and Server in one view."
    - "Next.js and TanStack Start: Unified context for both sides of the app."
    - "Monorepo Strategy: How to scope an Agent to a specific package."
- slide_number: 10
  heading: "Guardrails & Automated Safety"
  points[3]:
    - "Pre-tool Hooks: Auto-formatting, ESLint, and Tests as entry gates."
    - "Code Review Agents: Using a second AI to audit the first."
    - "Agent-ref-id: Using 'lovable-tagger' for auto-tagging AI vs. Human code."
- slide_number: 11
  heading: "Test-Driven Vibe Coding (TDVC)"
  points[3]:
    - "The pace of generation requires the pace of verification."
    - "Workflow: Failing Test -> AI Generation -> Green Light."
    - "Testing is more important now than it was in the manual era."
- slide_number: 12
  heading: "Pruning & Knowledge Compression"
  points[3]:
    - "Context Windows: Using 'Smol' or compact formats to save tokens."
    - "Pruning: Periodically summarizing the chat and starting fresh."
    - "Dual Documentation: READMEs for Humans vs. .md summaries for Agents."
- slide_number: 13
  heading: "The Toolbox (Search Before Building)"
  points[4]:
    - "skills.sh: Pre-built agent skills library."
    - "Awesome-Copilot: Best practices for GitHub tools."
    - "Souls.directory: Advanced Claude/Agent prompts."
    - "app.aitmpl.com/agents: Ready-to-use agent templates."
- slide_number: 14
  heading: "The Local Engine"
  points[3]:
    - "Privacy and Speed: Running LLMs locally."
    - "llmfit: One command to see what your hardware can actually handle."
    - "Finding the 'Sweet Spot' between VRAM and model quality."
- slide_number: 15
  heading: "Mindset: Architect, Not Coder"
  points[3]:
    - "You are a Product Owner now; you manage the 'output' of the AI."
    - "Cognitive Offloading: Use AI for the 'grunt work,' save your brain for the 'Hard Logic'."
    - "The Warning: You must be able to debug manually or you will be locked out of your own production."